Class RequestFormParams

java.lang.Object

java.util.ArrayList<RequestFormParam>
org.apache.juneau.rest.httppart.RequestFormParams
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<RequestFormParam>, java.util.Collection<RequestFormParam>, java.util.List<RequestFormParam>, java.util.RandomAccess
public class RequestFormParams
extends java.util.ArrayList<RequestFormParam>
Represents the parsed form-data parameters in an HTTP request.

The RequestFormParams object is the API for accessing the HTTP request content as form data. It can be accessed by passing it as a parameter on your REST Java method:

@RestPost(...) public Object myMethod(RequestFormParams formData) {...}

Example:

@RestPost(...) public Object myMethod(RequestFormParams formData) { // Get query parameters converted to various types. int p1 = formData.get("p1").asInteger().orElse(0); String p2 = formData.get("p2").orElse(null); UUID p3 = formData.get("p3").as(UUID.class).orElse(null); }

Note that this object does NOT take GET parameters into account and only returns values found in the content of the request.

Some important methods on this class are:

  • RequestFormParams
    • Methods for retrieving form data parameters:
      • contains(String)
      • containsAny(String...)
      • get(Class)
      • get(String)

      • getLast(String)
    • Methods overridding form data parameters:
      • add(NameValuePair...)

      • addDefault(List)
      • addDefault(NameValuePair...)
      • addDefault(String,String)
      • remove(String)
      • set(NameValuePair...)
      • set(String,Object)
    • Other methods:
      • asQueryString()
      • copy()
      • isEmpty()
  • RequestFormParam
  • FormData
